<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="busy-adj">busy <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'bɪzi/    美 /'bɪzi/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>忙的；忙碌的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Could I have a word with you, if you’re not too busy?
你若不太忙的话，我跟你说句话行吗?</p></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) busy with sth / sb:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I am so busy with my classes that I just don’t have time to exercise. 
我课业太忙，所以没时间锻炼。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) busy doing sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Right now, I’m busy preparing for the National College Entrance Examination.
目前，我正忙着准备高考。</p><footer>北师大⑤ – 13</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>繁忙的 (一段时间)； 热闹的 (地点)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a busy morning / spring
繁忙的早上/春天</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The shops are very busy before Christmas. 
圣诞节前商店里很热闹。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>(尤指电话线) 被占用的；没空的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’m sorry, sir. The line is busy.
对不起，先生，电话占线。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Every time I call the number, I get a <strong>busy signal</strong>. 
我每次拨打那个号码都会听到忙音。</p></div></div>